## Executive summary

Phases A‚ÄìK of the CT/RT hard-constraint implementation (rest-day allocation for Swiss AZG / BAR CCT compliance) have been validated end-to-end against the QA stack. All 13 test cases ‚Äî 10 functional + 3 negatives ‚Äî pass cleanly with the minimal-constraint test profile.

Two non-trivial regressions were discovered and fixed during validation:

1. **Partitioner flag-propagation bug** (TC-02 initial failure ‚Üí TC-02 retest pass). Phase A flags were set on the top-level `preprocessed_data` but lost when `SolverPartitioner.solve_partition()` built fresh per-partition `PreprocessedData` objects. Fixed by threading `rt_replannable`/`ct_replannable` through `solve_with_checkpointing ‚Üí solve_partition ‚Üí preprocess_data()`. Covered by 3-file surgical diff (see changelog & `CT_RT_ROUND1_INVESTIGATION_PLAN.md`).

2. **CP-SAT worker OOM** (mid-solve container crash). OR-Tools auto-detected 32 workers on the host; each worker cloned the presolved model ‚Üí 10.2 GiB anon-RSS ‚Üí kernel OOM-kill ‚Üí docker restarted the container ‚Üí in-memory job_manager wiped ‚Üí 404 on `/solver/status/{job_id}`. Fixed by capping workers in `solver/model.py:736` via `CFF_SOLVER_NUM_WORKERS` env var (default 4). Post-fix peak memory during the largest test was 3.6 GiB on an 8 GiB container.

Two operational fixes bundled alongside:

- `mock_data_v2/database_application_v2/local_deploy.sh::clean_pgdata()` rewritten to delete the data directory via a root-alpine container mounting the parent (previously failed with `rm: Permission denied on ./data/postgres_qa`).
- Phase J stdout logging added at `analysis/constraint_analyzers/lc_08_monthly_rest_analyzer.py:493-504` so `ct_rt_compliance_alerts` are observable via `docker logs` (they are currently NOT persisted in `planner_output.metadata`, which only stores `analysis_summary`).

